edu.stanford.math.plex4.metric.interfaces

Interface AbstractIntMetricSpace

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    AbstractObjectMetricSpace<T>, AbstractSearchableMetricSpace<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EuclideanMetricSpace, ExplicitLandmarkSelector, ExplicitMetricSpace, GeometricSimplexStream, KDEuclideanMetricSpace, LandmarkSelector, MaxMinLandmarkSelector, ObjectSearchableFiniteMetricSpace, RandomLandmarkSelector, SkeletalMetric

    public interface AbstractIntMetricSpace
    This interface defines the functionality of a finite metric space where the objects are indexed by integers. Note that the indices are designed to be in the range {0, ..., size - 1}.
    Author:
    Andrew Tausz
